summary: Guys, has anyone discussed what it might mean/ the general idea that Sansa was the first to reunite with each of her remaining...
body:
Guys, has anyone discussed what it might mean/ the general idea that Sansa was the first to reunite with each of her remaining siblings? 

Like, she was the first to reunite with Jon, even though everyone knew he would be at Castle Black so it wasn’t as if he was impossible to find.

She was the first to reunite with Bran, which okay, she was the only one at Winterfell when he arrive so I’ll give you that. But also he arrived RIGHT after Jon left SoOoOo. 

And she was the first to reunite with Arya, despite the fact that Bran was there also. I mean sort of there. But still… the point is, she has been the first FAMILY face each of them have seen in a long ass time. 

Maybe it means nothing but also maybe it means she’s the most Starkey Stark of all Starks?!?!

summary: In any case, Sansa’s journey - not to mention Sophie Turner’s performance - quietly became one of the show’s most dynamic after...
caption:
In any case, Sansa’s journey - not to mention Sophie Turner’s performance - quietly became one of the show’s most dynamic after she became Joffrey’s fiancée slash hostage. That might not have been immediately obvious given how much splahier her siblings’ storylines were. Her sister was becoming a warrior; her brothers were becoming generals and… well, whatever the Three-Eyed Raven is. But Sansa, dropped straight into the viper’s nest of King’s Landing, had to fight for her survival through a polite smile stifling a scream. She had to hide her true allegiances, shapeshift to please people without crossing too many wires, and prove her worth every minute of every day to convince leereing enemies they wouldn’t rather see her dead. While adversaries like Cersei, Ramsay Bolton, and even Petyr “Littlefinger” Baelish wrote her off as the silly teen that came to King’s Landing with stars in her eyes, Sansa withstood horrific abuse and learned how to evade their most nefarious plans by reflecting what they wanted to see, all while strengthening her own resolve to beat them when the time came. She came, she saw - and eventually, finally- she conquered.


Sansa’s impressive rise from imprisoned teen to the Lady of Winterfell (via Variety)

description:
Different Roads Sometimes Lead to the Same Castle 

“Remember when father used to tell us stories about Robert’s rebellion? Robb and I loved those stories, we dreamt that someday we’d ride side by side into battle. Father always made it out to be more glorious than it probably was.”
On the eve of danger, the four remaining Stark kids settle into what used to be their Lord Father’s bed and tell their own stories.

I said I wanted it, so…you know, write the fic you want to see in the world

summary: Predictions for GOT802
body:
Predictions for GOT802

  • Jaime trial goes Badly and he ends up in a cell
  • Dany tries to right things with Sansa and, being a somewhat smart ruler in the show, seeks out the counsel of the only high Lady she has left (RIP Olenna and Ellaria)
  • Sansa makes some comment on the lines of “we need all the allies we can get and he’s a smart battle tactician”
  • and also maybe “he broke a vow but he upheld his vow to defend the innocent” (since Aerys was going to burn down KL) and that will speak to Dany’s good heart and mission to break the wheel
  • Dany muses and decides to trust him and let him live
  • Uneasy peace between the two
  • Still no idea what to do about all the food though

summary:
Arya: So... What do you do when you like a boy? Asking for a friend.
Sansa: Laugh at his jokes. Oh, and you should do a little...
body:
Arya: So... What do you do when you like a boy? Asking for a friend.
Sansa: Laugh at his jokes. Oh, and you should do a little twirl when you leave the room and make sure he watches you walk away.
Arya: That’s the stupidest fucking thing I’ve ever heard.
Later, as Arya grins like a fool:
Sansa, smirking: Did you twirl? 
Arya:...
Arya: Yes.
